Create an External Activation Platform

Create an external activation platform in a Data Cloud Developer Edition org to help you reach your customers on your platform.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Developer Edition
Click the gear icon and click Data Cloud Setup.
Click External Activation Platform.
Click New.
Enter information about the platform that you want displayed for the Data Cloud admin. A preview appears on the right-hand side.
IMPORTANT The Developer Name you create in Data Cloud is needed later when you create custom metadata.
Click Next.
For each field:
Configure the required AccountId field by clicking the dropdown button. Click Edit.
In the Help Text, provide instructions for your Data Cloud admin on how to find their AccountId.
NOTE The Value stored in the AccountId field is in the file path and metadata file so you know where to ingest the data.
If you’d like to add more fields, click Save & Add. If you’re done adding fields, click Save & Close.
Click Next.
Select at least one Contact Point (also known as identifiers) you want to receive.
NOTE Select a hash method for Phone Number and Email Address Contact Points.
Click Next.
Select your Activation Schedule, Delivery Platform, and Data Delivery Options.
WARNING Enter the S3 Bucket Name where you want segments delivered. We ask for your S3 AccessKey and SecretKey when you create custom metadata.
Click Save.

Your external activation platform is created.
